<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-14T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="843" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d843">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador In Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-14T21:00:00+01:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 14, 1914, 9 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>114. Cannot assurances be obtained from England and France that purely
                            commercial cables to America will not be held up? Italy has asked our
                            aid regarding this matter. Complaints are made from a good source.
                            American trade greatly suffering.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>